        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We plan to observe the Bullet cluster in the 96-104 GHz frequency range,
and have a mosaic of 39 pointings covering a total of 3.0x3.0 arcmin over
the entire merging cluster with a sensitivity of 35microJy/beam.
Sensitivity is computed over the whole frequency width (7.5GHz), as we are
looking for a tiny effect in continuum.

The proposed observations will result in a 1sigma sensitivity of ~35 microJy/beam
(~0.6 mK) which is sufficient to detect and characterize the expected SZE from
the Bullet cluster (assuming that the temperature is above 5 keV, which is true 
for almost the entire cluster merger region).

Angular extents: The angular extent of the radio halos of
size 1 Mpc2 at the redshifts of the clusters (z ~0.2-0.6) is ~3x3 squared
arcminute.
The combination of baselines of main and ACA configurations will lead to
good uv-coverage, resulting in high-sensitivity, high-resolution images.

ACA is crucial to detect the most extended features up to 28arcsec.

Long tracks in u-v space are needed for good
visibility coverage, which is crucial for detecting faint, extended features,
as well as for the required sensitivity. </prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
