    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose observations of the ‘bullet’ cluster of galaxies – 1E 065756 – which consists of two sub-clusters in the process of merging, using both the main array and the ACA at 90 GHz. 
Australia Telescope Compact Array (ATCA) observations in 2009 and 2010 yielded robust high-resolution detection of a complex combination of the SZE and diffuse emission from the merger at 18 GHz. High-sensitivity observations with the same uv-coverage (10-20 arcsec resolution and 40-80 arcsec FOV) are needed to separate out the two effects. 
ALMA is the only instrument in the world that is capable of an FOV of 42 arcsec at 90 GHz, and therefore of obtaining a significant uv-coverage overlap with our ATCA observations. 
We intend to use ALMA to image a single pointing centered around the maximum SZ effect dip observed at 18 GHz, and use this ALMA image to subtract the SZ effect from the ATCA image and recover the diffuse emission that has been masked by the SZ effect. 
These observations together with ATCA data along with existing comprehensive X-ray, optical, low-resolution SZE and weak-lensing data will enable detailed analyses of the density-temperature structure and dynamics of this cluster.</prp:abstract>
